He, whose firm understanding obtains a command over his words, a
command over his thoughts, and a command over his whole body, may
justly be called a Triple-Commander.

The man who exerts this triple self-command with respect to all
animated creatures, wholly subduing both lust and wrath, shall by
those means attain Beatitude.
